==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embar
<hw>Em*bar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Embarred</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Embanking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>em-</ets>
+ <ets>bar</ets>: cf. F. <ets>embarrer</ets>. Cf.
<er>Embargo</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To bar or shut in; to inclose
securely, as with bars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where fast <qex>embarred</qex> in mighty brazen wall.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To stop; to hinder by prohibition; to block
up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>embarred</qex> all further trade.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embarcation</ent>⟦br⟧
